In .NET MAUI, use `Application.Current.RequestedTheme` and the `RequestedThemeChanged` event. To override, set `Application.Current.UserAppTheme`.

```csharp
// Detect current system theme
AppTheme currentTheme = Application.Current.RequestedTheme;
// Returns AppTheme.Light, AppTheme.Dark, or AppTheme.Unspecified

// Subscribe to real-time theme changes
Application.Current.RequestedThemeChanged += (s, e) =>
{
    AppTheme newTheme = e.RequestedTheme;
    Debug.WriteLine($"Theme changed to: {newTheme}");
    // Update your UI here
};

// Force a specific theme (overrides system setting)
Application.Current.UserAppTheme = AppTheme.Dark;

// Revert to following the system setting
Application.Current.UserAppTheme = AppTheme.Unspecified;
```

**A fuller pattern** — a service you can inject via DI:

```csharp
public class ThemeService
{
    public ThemeService()
    {
        Application.Current.RequestedThemeChanged += OnSystemThemeChanged;
    }

    public AppTheme Current =>
        Application.Current.UserAppTheme != AppTheme.Unspecified
            ? Application.Current.UserAppTheme
            : Application.Current.RequestedTheme;

    public void SetTheme(AppTheme theme) =>
        Application.Current.UserAppTheme = theme;  // Unspecified = follow system

    private void OnSystemThemeChanged(object sender, AppThemeChangedEventArgs e)
    {
        Debug.WriteLine($"System theme → {e.RequestedTheme}");
        WeakReferenceMessenger.Default.Send(new ThemeChangedMessage(e.RequestedTheme));
    }
}
```

**Key points:**

| API | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `RequestedTheme` | Read the OS-level theme |
| `RequestedThemeChanged` | React when the user toggles dark mode in device settings |
| `UserAppTheme` | Override the theme app-wide (`Unspecified` = follow system) |
| `AppThemeBinding` | XAML markup for per-theme values (colors, images, etc.) |

**XAML example** — values that swap automatically:

```xml
<Label Text="Hello"
       TextColor="{AppThemeBinding Light=Black, Dark=White}" />
```

`AppThemeBinding` respects `UserAppTheme` when set, otherwise follows the system.
